20using BlockConstIterator = ZoneVector<BasicBlock*>::const_iterator;

24class Graph final : public ZoneObject {
25 public:
26 static Graph* New(Zone* zone, bool is_osr) {
27 return zone->New<Graph>(zone, is_osr);
28 }
29
30 // Shouldn't be used directly; public so that Zone::New can access it.
31 Graph(Zone* zone, bool is_osr)
32 : blocks_(zone),
33 root_(zone),
34 osr_values_(zone),
35 smi_(zone),
36 tagged_index_(zone),
37 int32_(zone),
38 uint32_(zone),
39 float_(zone),
40 external_references_(zone),
41 parameters_(zone),
42 allocations_(zone),
43 register_inputs_(),
44 constants_(zone),
45 inlined_functions_(zone),
46 is_osr_(is_osr),
47 scope_infos_(zone) {}
48
49 BasicBlock* operator[](int i) { return blocks_[i]; }
50 const BasicBlock* operator[](int i) const { return blocks_[i]; }
51
52 int num_blocks() const { return static_cast<int>(blocks_.size()); }
53
54 BlockConstIterator begin() const { return blocks_.begin(); }
55 BlockConstIterator end() const { return blocks_.end(); }
56 BlockConstReverseIterator rbegin() const { return blocks_.rbegin(); }
57 BlockConstReverseIterator rend() const { return blocks_.rend(); }
58
59 BasicBlock* last_block() const { return blocks_.back(); }
60
61 void Add(BasicBlock* block) { blocks_.push_back(block); }
62
63 uint32_t tagged_stack_slots() const { return tagged_stack_slots_; }
64 uint32_t untagged_stack_slots() const { return untagged_stack_slots_; }
65 uint32_t max_call_stack_args() const { return max_call_stack_args_; }
66 uint32_t max_deopted_stack_size() const { return max_deopted_stack_size_; }
67 void set_tagged_stack_slots(uint32_t stack_slots) {
68 DCHECK_EQ(kMaxUInt32, tagged_stack_slots_);
69 DCHECK_NE(kMaxUInt32, stack_slots);
70 tagged_stack_slots_ = stack_slots;
71 }
72 void set_untagged_stack_slots(uint32_t stack_slots) {
73 DCHECK_EQ(kMaxUInt32, untagged_stack_slots_);
74 DCHECK_NE(kMaxUInt32, stack_slots);
75 untagged_stack_slots_ = stack_slots;
76 }
77 void set_max_call_stack_args(uint32_t stack_slots) {
78 DCHECK_EQ(kMaxUInt32, max_call_stack_args_);
79 DCHECK_NE(kMaxUInt32, stack_slots);
80 max_call_stack_args_ = stack_slots;
81 }
82 void set_max_deopted_stack_size(uint32_t size) {
83 DCHECK_EQ(kMaxUInt32, max_deopted_stack_size_);
84 DCHECK_NE(kMaxUInt32, size);
85 max_deopted_stack_size_ = size;
86 }

88 int total_inlined_bytecode_size() const {
89 return total_inlined_bytecode_size_;
90 }
91 void add_inlined_bytecode_size(int size) {
92 total_inlined_bytecode_size_ += size;
93 }

118 return inlined_functions_;
119 }

122
123 bool is_osr() const { return is_osr_; }
124 uint32_t min_maglev_stackslots_for_unoptimized_frame_size() {
125 DCHECK(is_osr());
126 if (osr_values().size() == 0) {
127 return InitialValue::stack_slot(0);
128 }
129 return osr_values().back()->stack_slot() + 1;
130 }

132 int NewObjectId() { return object_ids_++; }

134 // Resolve the scope info of a context value.
135 // An empty result means we don't statically know the context's scope.
136 compiler::OptionalScopeInfoRef TryGetScopeInfo(
137 ValueNode* context, compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker) {
138 auto it = scope_infos_.find(context);
139 if (it != scope_infos_.end()) {
140 return it->second;
141 }
142 compiler::OptionalScopeInfoRef res;
143 if (auto context_const = context->TryCast<Constant>()) {
144 res = context_const->object().AsContext().scope_info(broker);
145 DCHECK(res->HasContext());
146 } else if (auto load = context->TryCast<LoadTaggedField>()) {
147 compiler::OptionalScopeInfoRef cur =
148 TryGetScopeInfo(load->input(0).node(), broker);
149 DCHECK(load->offset() ==
150 Context::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::EXTENSION_INDEX) ||
151 load->offset() ==
152 Context::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX));
153 if (load->offset() ==
154 Context::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::EXTENSION_INDEX)) {
155 res = cur;
156 } else if (load->offset() ==
157 Context::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX)) {
158 if (cur.has_value()) {
159 cur = (*cur).OuterScopeInfo(broker);
160 while (!cur->HasContext() && cur->HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
161 cur = cur->OuterScopeInfo(broker);
162 }
163 if (cur->HasContext()) {
164 res = cur;
165 }
166 }
167 }
168 } else if (context->Is<InitialValue>()) {
169 // We should only fail to keep track of initial contexts originating from
170 // the OSR prequel.
171 // TODO(olivf): Keep track of contexts when analyzing OSR Prequel.
172 DCHECK(is_osr());
173 } else {
174 // Any context created within a function must be registered in
175 // graph()->scope_infos(). Initial contexts must be registered before
176 // BuildBody. We don't track context in generators (yet) and around eval
177 // the bytecode compiler creates contexts by calling
178 // Runtime::kNewFunctionInfo directly.
179 DCHECK(context->Is<Phi>() || context->Is<GeneratorRestoreRegister>() ||
180 context->Is<RegisterInput>() || context->Is<CallRuntime>());
181 }
182 return scope_infos_[context] = res;
183 }
184
185 void record_scope_info(ValueNode* context,
186 compiler::OptionalScopeInfoRef scope_info) {
187 scope_infos_[context] = scope_info;
188 }
189
190 private:
191 uint32_t tagged_stack_slots_ = kMaxUInt32;
192 uint32_t untagged_stack_slots_ = kMaxUInt32;
193 uint32_t max_call_stack_args_ = kMaxUInt32;
194 uint32_t max_deopted_stack_size_ = kMaxUInt32;
195 ZoneVector<BasicBlock*> blocks_;
196 ZoneMap<RootIndex, RootConstant*> root_;
197 ZoneVector<InitialValue*> osr_values_;
198 ZoneMap<int, SmiConstant*> smi_;
199 ZoneMap<int, TaggedIndexConstant*> tagged_index_;
200 ZoneMap<int32_t, Int32Constant*> int32_;
201 ZoneMap<uint32_t, Uint32Constant*> uint32_;
202 // Use the bits of the float as the key.
203 ZoneMap<uint64_t, Float64Constant*> float_;
204 ZoneMap<Address, ExternalConstant*> external_references_;
205 ZoneVector<InitialValue*> parameters_;
206 ZoneMap<InlinedAllocation*, AllocationDependencies> allocations_;
207 RegList register_inputs_;
208 compiler::ZoneRefMap<compiler::ObjectRef, Constant*> constants_;
209 ZoneVector<OptimizedCompilationInfo::InlinedFunctionHolder>
210 inlined_functions_;
211 bool has_recursive_calls_ = false;
212 int total_inlined_bytecode_size_ = 0;
213 bool is_osr_ = false;
214 int object_ids_ = 0;
215 ZoneUnorderedMap<ValueNode*, compiler::OptionalScopeInfoRef> scope_infos_;
216};
